Vice President Mike Pence met with President Nursultan Nazarbayev of Kazakhstan to discuss various topics. They talked about Kazakhstan's support for the United States' South Asia strategy, efforts to strengthen U.S.-Kazakhstani business partnerships, and their collaboration on nuclear nonproliferation. Pence emphasized the importance of Kazakhstan's work on anti-corruption and civil liberties, particularly in protecting religious freedoms. He also thanked Nazarbayev for their cooperation on counterterrorism. Both leaders reaffirmed their commitment to Kazakhstan's sovereignty and territorial integrity and welcomed the enhanced strategic partnership between the two countries.